                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363 Manchuria/182: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-26T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 26, 1935—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>68. Your 93, April 26, 5 p.m. Representatives of Standard-Vacuum plan to call at
                    Department April 29 for further discussion.</p>
                <p>Meanwhile, in the light of Department’s views as set forth in penultimate
                    paragraph of its 67, April 24, 7 p.m., you should make no commitment to any
                    other line of procedure.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
